The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to match sub-articles to their corresponding main articles in Wikipedia. This falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL).
